Defendant Renee L Russell in court with attorney Timothy T. Kay.  Mary C. Brejcha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Plea colloquy.

Court will not permit a no contest plea.  Parties agree to enter a guilty plea.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld Sentence of:
(Credit - 0 days)

Term of Probation: 3 Years Can be transferred to Jefferson County

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year of probation with last 20 hours to be complete by November 2017;
- No contact with with medical professionals without approval of probation agent until in an emergency.
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge

Costs: $268.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00
(To be paid at the rate of $50.00  per month commencing 5-1-15 and/or 52 hours of community service to be completed by completion of probation.  Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.)

Condition Time: 30 days Huber NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - Stayed and to be used at the agent's discretion.  Can be served in Jefferson County
